OL,3,CGatwick Airport's second runway legal
OL,4,Cchallenge to be heard at High Court
OL,6,FCagne is set to argue that consent
OL,7,Fshould not have been granted on
OL,8,Fseveral grounds, including that there
OL,9,Fwas an unlawful failure to consider
OL,10,Fharms caused by noise and errors when
OL,11,Fconsidering greenhouse gas emissions
OL,12,Ffrom inbound flights.
OL,14,FThe DfT and the airport's owner,
OL,15,FGatwick Airport Limited (GAL), are
OL,16,Fopposing the challenge.
OL,18,FThe hearing before Mr Justice Mould is
OL,19,Fdue to begin at 10.30am at the Royal
OL,20,FCourts of Justice in London, and is
OL,21,Fexpected to conclude on Friday.
